<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="49" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,942,1975]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1843,1867]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from the Latin &quot; 
<emphasis box="[845,909,1844,1867]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">minut</emphasis>
&quot;, corresponding to the smaller size of the adult compared with other species of the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,942,1975]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1915,1939]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">Remarks.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[378,476,1914,1938]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">holotype</typeStatus>
is partly destroyed. However, the external characters are obviously distinguishable from other species of the genus by the longer and stronger white stripe on ventral margin of cell of the forewing.
</paragraph>
